title: Verify enable the feature through wbeui
custom_summary: Verify enable the feature through wbeui
custom_preconds:
1. User is logged in
2. Navigate to the configuration sidebar in the Security Cloud Platform.
custom_steps:
1. Locate "URL Case Sensitivity Match" configuration item.
2. Click on the "Edit" button.
3. Wait for the popup window to appear.
4. Locate the toggle switch for enabling/disabling the configuration.
    1. Verify the toggle is in disable state
    2. Check for the wording is â€œDisabledâ€?
5. Click on the toggle switch to enable the configuration.
6. Click on the "Save" button.
7. Verify that the configuration is enabled:
    1. Check for the indicator is green.
    2. Verify that the wording of the configuration item changes to "Enabled".
8. Check the tenant's tenant_admin_feature_config.json
custom_expected: tenant_admin_feature_config.json should get update and the config item should set to  "case-insensitive-url": {"enabled": true} in tenant_admin_feature_config.json
